Class Person

  • java.lang.Object
    • Person
  • public class Person
extends Object
    This class creates a Person and you can change their name, surname, age and gender; print their content; compare it with other people....
    Version:
    13/09/2022
    Author:
    Paula Díaz Álvarez

    • Constructor Detail

      • Person

        public Person()
        Default constructor to create a person with random values. It assigns a random name (if it is a male "Yuri" and if it's a female "Valentina"), random surname, random age between [MIN_AGE_VALUE,MAX_AGE_VALUE], and a random gender

      • Person

        public Person​(int age)
        Constructor to create a person with a given age and the rest of the fields are random as the default constructor
        Parameters:
        age - It's the age that is set to the person

      • Person

              String surname)

        public void setAge​(int age)
        Changes the value of the age of the person. If the new value for the age is less than MIN_AGE_VALUE or higher than MAX_AGE_VALUE, the age will not be updated and an error message will appear depending on the error.
        Parameters:
        age - It's the age that is set to the person

        Returns:

      • isAGirl

        public boolean isAGirl()
        Asks if the person is a girl. If gender is female, it's a girl. Else, it's a boy (not a girl)
        Returns:
        True if the gender of the person is female

      • print1

        public void print1()
        Prints the contents of name,surname, age and gender of the person into the computer's console (display). If the gender is equal to FEMALE_VALUE, it prints female. If not, it prints male

      • print2

        public void print2()
        Prints the value of name,surname, age and gender of the person into the computer's console (display). If the gender is equal to FEMALE_VALUE, it prints female. If not, it prints male

      • toString

        public String toString()
        Returns a line that contains the value of name, surname, age and gender of the person. If the gender is equal to FEMALE_VALUE, it prints female. If not, it prints male
        Overrides:
        toString in class Object
        Returns:
        Line corresponding to all the values of the fields of the person

      • getHashCode

        public String getHashCode()
        Returns a line looking like a code, including the value of name, surname, age and gender of the person. The name and the surname are written in Upper Case.
        Returns:
        Line looking like a code representing the values of the fields of the class

      • HashCode

        public String HashCode()
        Creates a line looking like a code, including the value of name, surname, age and gender of the person. It only writes the first 3 letters of the name and the surname in Upper Case.
        Returns:
        Line looking like a code representing the values of the fields of the class
